# Code Quality Standards

This project maintains strict code quality standards as demonstrated in [backend/utils.py](mdc:backend/utils.py).

## Python Standards

### Type Hints
- All functions must include return type hints
- All parameters must be typed
- Use `typing` module for complex types
- Prefer `Final` for constants

### Documentation
- Module-level docstrings explaining purpose
- Function docstrings in NumPy format
- Clear inline comments for complex logic
- Type hints as documentation

### Error Handling
- Handle all external API calls
- Use appropriate exception types
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Fail gracefully when possible

### Code Organization
- Follow SOLID principles
- Keep functions pure when possible
- Use constants for configuration
- Early environment variable loading
- Clear separation of concerns

### Testing
- All new code requires tests
- Test error cases
- Test edge cases
- Mock external dependencies

### Style
- Follow PEP 8
- Use meaningful variable names
- Keep functions focused and small
- Document any linter exceptions
